Absurdity	#497.	 macaronic, punning. foolish &c.
Imbecility. Folly	#499.	 simious. foolish, silly, senseless, irrational, insensate, nonsensical, inept
Imbecility. Folly	#499.	 eccentric &c. (crazed). [Applied to actions] foolish, unwise, injudicious, improper, unreasonable, without reason, ridiculous, absurd, idiotic, silly, stupid, asinine
Caprice	#608.	 penny wise and pound foolish
Waste	#638.	 penny wise and pound foolish. Phr. magno conatu magnas nugas [Lat.]
Unskillfulness	#699.	 misconducted, foolish, wild
Unskillfulness	#699.	 penny wise and pound foolish &c. (inconsistent). Phr. one's fingers being all thumbs
Prodigality	#818.	 full-handed &c. (liberal). penny wise and pound foolish. Adv. with an unsparing hand
Disrepute	#874.	 look blue, look foolish, look like a fool
Humility	#879.	 hang one's head, look foolish, feel small. render humble
